Doris Nolan https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doris_Nolan 0 Doris Nolan (July 14, 1916 – July 29, 1998) was an American actress best known for her Broadway roles and her appearance in the 1938 movie Holiday. She appeared in a number of plays and Hollywood movies during the 1930s and 1940s. Later she moved to Britain, where she made guest appearances on British television shows.
